  "texts": [
    "On Offset Bias dataset with Llama base judge, the BTL2 judge doubles Pearson's r, Spearman's ρ, and Kendall's τ of the base judges.",
    "We delve deeper into how the improvements arise in Section B.4, where we report confusion matrices between human and predicted scores.",
    "In Figure 10, the base judge fails to predict frequent scores 5 and 6.",
    "Both the LS and MN judges learn to predict them, and in this way improve upon the base judge.",
    "Computation time: We report the training and inference times of quantitative judges, and compare them to those of base judges and fine-tuning them, in Section C. The quantitative judges can be trained in an order of magnitude less time than supervised fine-tuning."
  ],
